            "updated_at": "Tue, 11/30/2021 - 10:14",
            "answer_part_1": "<p>Many parents have a hard time leaving their child in “the hands” of others, that might be a familiar person such as a grandparent, or a complete stranger such as a childminder at the child care setting. If you can, try to spend some time with the other caregiver and your child together so that you can observe how they interact.</p>",
            "answer_part_2": "<p>You could share your child’s daily schedule and the rules that you like the caregiver to follow. You can even prepare this in writing. You can agree together on how you can be in contact when the child is with the caregiver, for example, via WhatsApp.</p>",
