            "type": "FAQ",
            "question": "What are the ways to improve my former partner’s relationship with my child?",
            "created_at": "Tue, 11/30/2021 - 10:08",
            "updated_at": "Tue, 11/30/2021 - 10:10",
            "answer_part_1": "<p>Even though you are not married to your former partner now, it is beneficial for the children to continue having a positive relationship. Both parents are important in the child’s development.  This is true even if the children do not live with the other parent.</p>",
            "answer_part_2": "<p>Avoid speaking negatively about your partner when the children are around. When children hear something negative about a parent—even if it’s true—they might take it personally as something bad or undesirable about themselves. Remember that your partner is and will always be the second parent and, therefore, a significant person for your child.</p>",
