            "created_at": "Tue, 11/30/2021 - 10:04",
            "updated_at": "Tue, 11/30/2021 - 10:05",
            "answer_part_1": "<p>Making connections in your new community is essential as your children get older so that they can have friends and adult role models that they see every day and who become part of their bigger “family.” If language is a challenge, perhaps you can find other families who speak your home language.  Perhaps there is a community organization they attend, with activities you can participate in with your child. </p>",
