            "type": "FAQ",
            "question": "Can I help my child learn?",
            "created_at": "Mon, 11/29/2021 - 18:03",
            "updated_at": "Mon, 11/29/2021 - 18:04",
            "answer_part_1": "<p>Yes, you can.  Be sure your children know that you think they are smart and able to do many things.  Praise them for trying challenging things (riding a bicycle, trying to write their names, drawing a picture of you, helping prepare food for the family).  By giving your children confidence, you are giving them a foundation for successful learning. At home, you do not need to give your children lessons.  Parents do not have to be “teachers.” </p>",
            "answer_part_2": "<p>Just watch what they like to do and share their interest when you have time.  For example, perhaps they are interested in cars and trucks.  You can watch them as they pass in the road.  You can talk about the different kinds of cars, count them, tell stories about where the trucks may be going and what they may carry.  When you show your child that you are interested and when you encourage your child’s learning, you are giving your child the most important gifts you have!</p>",
            "chatbot_subcategory": 110136,
