            "id": 60206,
            "type": "FAQ",
            "question": "How will I know if my children are learning what they need for school success?",
            "created_at": "Mon, 11/29/2021 - 18:01",
            "updated_at": "Mon, 11/29/2021 - 18:02",
            "answer_part_1": "<p>Your children will gain many of the skills needed for school better and faster if encouraged to explore, play, and create.  If your children are content and engaged in their play, you know that your children are learning. Remember also that being “ready” for school is not just knowing letters and numbers (although this is helpful).</p>",
            "answer_part_2": "<p>Readiness also includes physical readiness (health, physical skills), social-emotional readiness (cooperation, understanding and managing feelings), language readiness (speaking and listening to others), and so on.  Your everyday activities and relationships with your child are helping to build this “readiness.”</p>",
            "chatbot_subcategory": 110136,
            "related_article": 2226,
            "mandatory": 1
