            "type": "FAQ",
            "question": " If my children hit, should I teach them by hitting them back?",
            "created_at": "Mon, 11/29/2021 - 17:46",
            "updated_at": "Mon, 11/29/2021 - 17:48",
            "answer_part_1": "<p>Instead of hitting back, first, calm yourself and your child.  Take a deep breath and remember that you are the adult.  You may need to gently hold your child’s hand while you say, “Hitting each other can hurt. That’s why we are gentle. It is OK to be angry, but it is not OK to hit and hurt someone. I see you are angry with me.”</p>",
            "answer_part_2": "<p>When your child has calmed down, you can say: “You can tell me ‘I do not want to stop playing now!’ but you may not hit.  I will help you remember.”</p>",
