            "type": "FAQ",
            "question": "Why does not my child listen to me?",
            "created_at": "Mon, 11/29/2021 - 17:40",
            "updated_at": "Mon, 11/29/2021 - 17:42",
            "answer_part_1": "<p>One of the reasons might be that your children are distracted. If you ask your child something, make sure that they can give full attention to your question. Turn off any devices, get down to your children’s height and look them in the eye. If your children do not want to listen, you can look disapprovingly and ask why they do not want to listen. Repeat and acknowledge what they say and express your point of view.</p>",
