            "question": "How to teach my child to share and cooperate?",
            "created_at": "Mon, 11/29/2021 - 17:30",
            "updated_at": "Mon, 11/29/2021 - 17:32",
            "answer_part_1": "<p>It is a slow process, and very young children do not understand that concept. You can get your child used to the idea of giving and getting back with simple back-and-forth games, giving your child something like a small ball, asking for it back, and repeating. Roll the ball to make it fun. When your toddler plays with others, try to have enough objects so that they do not have to share the most special things.</p>",
