            "type": "FAQ",
            "question": "How can I play with my child if I am too busy or too tired?",
            "created_at": "Mon, 11/29/2021 - 16:28",
            "updated_at": "Mon, 11/29/2021 - 16:30",
            "answer_part_1": "<p>Life is difficult for a busy or overwhelmed parent. However, play is important for your child’s development and learning. It is also essential as a way to connect with your child. There are ways to play even when you are exhausted. For example, perhaps you can give your children some objects from the kitchen (spoons, cups) or some pillows that they can pile up to make a little “house.”</p>",
