            "answer_part_1": "<p>Yes, there is always help, and there is always hope. If you feel this way, please reach out to someone who can support you. This may be a caring family member, a good friend, or a health professional. Because of depression or trauma in your life, you may feel hopeless right now. </p>",
            "answer_part_2": "<p>But if you, or someone in your family, has those feelings, be sure there is help available. Staying mentally healthy is important for you, and your children and family. If you are not well, it affects your parenting capacity. Reach out and seek help! (CO can add relevant SOS/hotlines, phones for counselling services etc.)</p>",
