            "question": "How do I deal with my concerns about my child with disability?",
            "created_at": "Tue, 11/23/2021 - 17:40",
            "updated_at": "Fri, 11/26/2021 - 10:16",
            "answer_part_1": "<p>It is not easy for a parent to accept or to deal with a child disability. Feel free to express how you feel about it and ask questions that will help you understand your child's condition and how can you support him or her. Your child, like all children, can make progress in his or her development despite disability and bring you much joy in your life. </p>",
            "answer_part_2": "<p>The advice section of the Bebbo app has many resources to help you understand disabilities. In the Games section, you will find many ideas on how you can support your child's development through daily interactions and play. Your health professional also can support you and answer many of your questions. Sharing your concerns and experiences with other parents of children who have disabilities might help alleviate some of your concerns and point you to additional resources.</p>",
            "chatbot_subcategory": 110201,
