            "id": 59356,
            "type": "FAQ",
            "question": "What can I do if there is physical abuse in my family?",
            "created_at": "Tue, 11/23/2021 - 17:40",
            "updated_at": "Fri, 11/26/2021 - 10:14",
            "answer_part_1": "<p>Sometimes abuse begins with small actions, but it usually becomes more frequent and more intense as time goes on. Children’s development can be seriously impacted if they see physical and emotional abuse or other violence in their homes.</p>",
            "answer_part_2": "<p>To protect yourself or a loved one, learn what help is available in your community and call the police if you or someone else is in danger. Telephone “hotlines” may be available, there may be community agencies that help people who are being abused, and health professionals are available to connect you with protective services.</p><p><strong>(NOTE FOR CO ADAPTATION: COs should specify the guidance with local police numbers or references to resources available within the country)</strong></p>",
            "chatbot_subcategory": 110201,
