            "question": "How do I know if my child is eating well?",
            "created_at": "Tue, 11/23/2021 - 17:40",
            "updated_at": "Fri, 11/26/2021 - 10:32",
            "answer_part_1": "<p>Babies and toddlers need foods from all five healthy food groups: vegetables, fruit, grain foods, dairy and protein. Healthy foods have nutrients that are important for growth, development and learning.</p>",
            "answer_part_2": "<p>Your child should avoid foods high in salt, saturated fat and sugar, foods low in fibre and nutrients, and drinks with caffeine and lots of sugar.</p>",
