            "answer_part_2": "<p>Sore nipples usually happen because your baby is not well positioned and attached at the breast. Putting up with it could make pain or discomfort worse, so it's important to get help from your midwife, health visitor or breastfeeding specialist as soon as you can. Thrush infections can sometimes happen when your nipples become cracked or damaged. Please consult your doctor.</p>",
