            "question": "How can I comfort my crying child?",
            "created_at": "Tue, 11/23/2021 - 17:40",
            "updated_at": "Fri, 11/26/2021 - 10:27",
            "answer_part_1": "<p>Crying is the only way your baby can tell you that something is the matter. Try not to ignore her! Pick her up, hold and rock her, check for a wet diaper or a need for a feed - by responding to your child cry, you are teaching her that she can depend on you. This is one of the most important lessons! You will quickly learn what helps to soothe your unique child. Some children, especially when they get a bit older, need to be left in a quiet place for a short time, not as a punishment but as a strategy to self-calm.</p>",
