            "question": "What are ways to help my child when we are going through a divorce ",
            "created_at": "Tue, 11/23/2021 - 17:40",
            "updated_at": "Fri, 11/26/2021 - 10:22",
            "answer_part_1": "<p>Children react to divorce in different ways, as they cope with difficult situations in different manners. They might feel like they have done something to cause the divorce, might feel anxious or act strange. As a parent, you need to know these are all normal reactions. The best you can do is let your children know that their emotions are okay and the divorce is not their responsibility. So try to talk to them, and listen to how they are feeling, even if it is hard for you. When listening to them, do not try to fix their problem. Instead, it is better if you acknowledge their feelings. This response will make your children feel like they can talk to you without making you feel bad.</p>",
            "answer_part_2": "<p>To help your children going through the divorce, there are certain golden rules to follow for your children's wellbeing:</p><ul><li>Try to be as calm as possible to make your children feel secure.</li>\t<li>Let them know the divorce is not their fault.</li>\t<li>Do not say anything bad about your spouse in front of the children.</li></ul><p>Children need to know that you and your spouse are on the same page. And of course, you can’t be your best for your children unless you’re also taking care of yourself.</p>",
