            "updated_at": "Tue, 12/28/2021 - 11:28",
            "answer_part_1": "<p>Severe Covid-19 cases in children are still rare, but cases persist and are increasing. First of all, to protect children from Covid-19, all adults in the family should be vaccinated. Children usually get infected from the adults. For school-age children, the recommendation is to wear a mask, to wash hands thoroughly and follow all protective measures in schools. In addition, in countries where child vaccination started, children  can get  a COVID-19 shot. However, for babies and toddlers, masks are not recommended, and you need to put in place some measures to protect your child. First, when you are outside, always wear a mask, avoid crowds, keep a safe distance from other people, and avoid seeing sick people.</p>",
            "answer_part_2": "<p>At home, wash your hands and teach others in your house to do the same. Also, wash your hands before breastfeeding, before handling your child and when you go back to your home before being outside. If you notice some symptoms in your child, the recommendation is to stay at home and contact your paediatrician.</p>",
