            "answer_part_1": "<p>As your child gets older, and perhaps begins preschool and goes into your community, she does need to learn safety rules about people she does not know. How can you do this without frightening her about all new people? First, it is important to be sure your child knows that her parents’ job is to keep her safe. Your supervision protects her from many kinds of harm. You should not leave your child with people that you do not know.</p>",
