            "answer_part_1": "<p>As a parent, it’s normal to feel tested to your limits sometimes. But sometimes, it can be worse than this. For example, suppose you feel exhausted, frustrated by your child’s challenging behaviour or worried about whether you’re doing the right thing. In that case, it can be hard to control your emotions and reactions. Not having enough support can also stretch your patience and ability to cope. If you feel like you might hurt your child right now, you need to stop, walk away, and take deep breaths.</p>",
